# Linear Conventions

Linear is used **company-wide** (not just app development): marketing, content, finance,
operations and legal all live here too. Because of that, **every ticket must be categorized**
so work stays findable across departments.

## Mandatory on every ticket

- **Team** — the owning team.
- **`Type` label** (flat labels, describe the nature of the work) — one of: `Feature`, `Bug`,
  `Improvement`, `Chore`, `Research`.
- **`Area` label** (label group → department) — one of: `Development`, `Design`, `Marketing`,
  `Content`, `Finance`, `Operations`, `Legal`.
- **Project** — link to the relevant project (e.g. "Odyssey") when applicable.
- Optional **`Platform`** label (group → `Albanie`, `Shared`) for product/engineering work.

## Assignment

- **All development-related tickets are assigned to Justin** (the engineer). If a ticket has
  `Area/Department: Development` (or a dev `Platform/App` label), set the assignee to Justin
  unless told otherwise.

## Creating tickets via MCP

- Before creating tickets, inspect existing teams/labels and **reuse** them — do not create
  duplicate labels with different casing/wording.
- Titles are concise and action-oriented; descriptions state intent + acceptance criteria.
- Group related work under an epic/parent where it helps.
